casebody.data:
Commonwealth versus Seth Gay.

See Stevens v. Dimond, 6 N. Hamp. R. 330; 1 Chitty on Crim. Law, (3d Amer. ed.) 290, (74); Revised Stat. c. 137, § 14.

Certiorari to the Municipal Court. In this case a complaint for a breach of one of the by-laws of Boston conceded “ against the form of the by-laws of said city,” &c., without concluding also against the form of the statute, and for this cause the proceedings were quashed. A like judgment was now entered for the same reason in the case of Commonwealth, in Certiorari, v. Worcester. See 3 Pick. 475.2
